com.customlbs.shared

Class Coordinate

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.customlbs.shared.Coordinate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class Coordinate
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Represents a Floor ID and a 2 dimensional Point.

    X and Y coordinate are your position on the current floor. The coordinate origin is the top-left corner in the building. Units are millimeter. Z coordinates are the ID of the floor (..., -1=Sub1, 0=Ground, 1=Floor1,...)

    For example if x=1500, y=10000, z=2 you are on the second floor and 1,5m from the left-most and 10m from the top-most corner in the building map.
